16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 49 O.S. 2021, Section 113,
18 as amended by Section 2, Chapter 226, O.S.L. 2024 (49 O.S.
19 Supp. 2024, Section 113), is amended to read as follows:
20 Section 113. A. In taking an acknowledgment, the
21 notarial officer must determine, either from personal
22 knowledge or from satisfactory evidence, that the person
23 appearing before the officer and making the acknowledgment is
24 the person whose true signature is on the instrument.
HB1578 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 B. In taking a verification upon oath or affirmation, the
2 notarial officer must determine, either from personal knowledge or
3 from satisfactory evidence, that the person appearing before the
4 officer and making the verification is the person whose true
5 signature is on the statement verified.
6 C. In witnessing or attesting a signature the notarial officer
7 must determine, either from personal knowledge or from satisfactory
8 evidence, that the signature is that of the person appearing before
9 the officer and named therein.
10 D. In certifying or attesting a copy of a document or other
11 item, the notarial officer must determine that the proffered copy is
12 a full, true, and accurate transcription or reproduction of that
13 which was copied. In the case of official records, only the
14 custodian of the official records may issue an official certified
15 copy.
16 E. In making or noting a protest of a negotiable instrument the
17 notarial officer must determine the matters set forth in Section 3-
18 509 of the Uniform Commercial Code.
19 F. A notarial officer has satisfactory evidence that a person
20 is the person whose true signature is on a document if that person
21 is personally known to the notarial officer, is identified upon the
22 oath or affirmation of a credible witness personally known to the
23 notarial officer or is identified on the basis of identification
24 documents.
HB1578 HFLR Page 2
