1 G. A notarial officer who performs a notarial act pursuant to
2 this section without first making in good faith the required
3 determination of the identity of the person appearing before the
4 notary shall be guilty of a misdemeanor felony and upon conviction
5 be subject to a fine not to exceed One Thousand Dollars ($1,000.00)
6 Five Thousand Dollars ($5,000.00), to imprisonment in the county
7 jail not to exceed ten (10) thirty (30) days, or both such fine and
8 imprisonment.
9 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
